  "doc_id": "51128",
  "text": "The springtime community was dominated by members of the Acidobacterium division. The cultured isolates from this group are facultatively or obligately anaerobic organotrophs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The moist conditions created at snowmelt may provide anaerobic microsites in the soil. This, with the high concentrations of organic N present at this time [CITATION_3] , may create the optimum conditions for these microbes.",
